15 WHEREAS, the story of Cornerstone Baptist Church PTC is one of triumph through the
16 grace and sustaining power of God, and it stands as an immovable witness to the truth that
17 God keeps His promise; and
18 WHEREAS, the congregation of this church has compiled an unparalleled record of
19 constructive, compassionate, and humanitarian service which it demonstrates daily through
20 open minds, open hearts, and open doors; and
21 WHEREAS, the members of Cornerstone Baptist Church PTC have a sincere desire to serve
22 the Lord and are wholeheartedly committed to spreading the Gospel of Jesus Christ; and
23 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this enduring example of God's message
24 of peace and love be recognized and congratulated for its innumerable good works rendered
25 on behalf of persons in need.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body recognize the rich history of Cornerstone Baptist Church PTC,
28 commend its 15 years of dedicated service to the Lord and its community, and extend the
29 warmest best wishes for its continued growth and success.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
32 Cornerstone Baptist Church PTC.
